> A good gravy has the power to transform a meal. Our festive gravy is just that and can be
> made in advance, simply reheating on the day to save you time. Its rich taste is the
> perfect accompaniment to your delicately flavoured turkey.

Heat @olive oil{5%tbsp} in a #pot{} over medium heat. Add @onion{1}(chopped) and cook
until softened, about ~{5%minutes}.

Add @plain flour{150%g} and stir to make a roux, cooking for about ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @boiling water{1500%ml} and @turkey stock powder{2%sachets}, whisking constantly
until the gravy thickens and is smooth.

Add @rosemary{1%bunch}(chopped) and @thyme{1%bunch}(chopped), then season to taste with
salt and black pepper. Cook for a further ~{10%minutes}.

Strain the gravy through a #fine sieve{} before serving.

> This gravy can be made in advance - simply reheat on the day to save you time.